<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName LSID="F7849DE9-42DC-53DA-ABB2-76945D6B1C0C" authority="Genkal in Nov. Syst. Nizsh. Rast. 15: 13, pl. 2, fig. 1. 1978." authorityName="Genkal in Nov. Syst. Nizsh. Rast. 15: 13, pl. 2, fig. 1. 1978." class="Coscinodiscophyceae" family="Stephanodiscaceae" genus="Stephanodiscus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Stephanodiscus makarovae" order="Thalassiosirales" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="makarovae">Stephanodiscus makarovae Genkal in Nov. Syst. Nizsh. Rast. 15: 13, pl. 2, fig. 1. 1978.</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Morphological description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
Frustule disciform, valve with slightly convex or concave centre, frequently flat, diameter 5.9-8.3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, striae are double, rarely triple, in numbers of 14-16 in 10 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
. One central process is present. Spines pointy, small-scale, growing from each costa (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. SEM images of species found in the transitional zone at Mykolaiv city (A, B, E-H valve views, C, D girdle views): A Minidiscus proschkinae with arrows showing rimoportula and marginal fultoportula B-D Skeletonema subsalsum with arrows showing marginal fultoportulae E Stephanodiscus hantzschii with arrow shown spines F Stephanodiscus makarovae with arrows showing marginal and central fultoportulae G, H Stephanodiscus minutulus with arrows showing spines and central fultoportula. Scale bars: 3 μm (A); 4 μm (B, F, H); 5 μm (C, D, G); 10 μm (E)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.178.64426.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545737" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">5F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
Planktonic in rivers, lakes and reservoirs, freshwater, but mainly in mesotrophic-eutrophic water bodies. In addition, reported occurrence of this species in high numbers in highly mineralized waters (
<bibRefCitation author="Genkal, SI" journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="241 - 248" refId="B37" refString="Genkal, SI, 2007. Morphology, taxonomy, ecology and distribution of small-sized species of the genus Stephanodiscus (Bacillariophyta). 2. Stephanodiscus makarovae. Botanical Journal 92 (2): 241 - 248" title="Morphology, taxonomy, ecology and distribution of small-sized species of the genus Stephanodiscus (Bacillariophyta). 2. Stephanodiscus makarovae." volume="92" year="2007">Genkal 2007</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1615/HydrobJ.v45.i6.40" author="Genkal, SI" journalOrPublisher="Hydrobiological Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="51 - 69" refId="B43" refString="Genkal, SI, Terenko, LM, Nesterova, DA, 2009. New data on flora of centric diatoms (Centrophyceae) of the Danube area of the Black Sea. Hydrobiological Journal 45 (4): 51 - 69, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1615/HydrobJ.v45.i6.40" title="New data on flora of centric diatoms (Centrophyceae) of the Danube area of the Black Sea." url="https://doi.org/10.1615/HydrobJ.v45.i6.40" volume="45" year="2009">Genkal et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Tsarenko, PM" journalOrPublisher="Gantner Verlag, Ruggell" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B127" refString="Tsarenko, PM, Wasser, SP, Nevo, E, 2009. Algae of Ukraine: diversity, nomenclature, taxonomy, ecology and geography. Vol. 2. Bacillariophyta. A.R.A. Gantner Verlag, Ruggell" title="Algae of Ukraine: diversity, nomenclature, taxonomy, ecology and geography. Vol. 2. Bacillariophyta. A. R. A." year="2009">Tsarenko et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Coscinodiscophyceae" family="Stephanodiscaceae" genus="Stephanodiscus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Stephanodiscus makarovae" order="Thalassiosirales" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="makarovae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Stephanodiscus makarovae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was observed downstream from Mykolaiv city in the Southern Bug River (Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Species composition of centric diatoms at the investigated sites near Mykolaiv city in the Southern Bug River in the year 2017 (2013 added for station 2)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DD3AC92F3D14B9FD95B22148C16CA677" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" tableUuid="DD3AC92F3D14B9FD95B22148C16CA677">1</tableCitation>
). It was observed in the Dnipro River and its reservoirs, the Danube River and in the coastal area of the Black Sea (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1615/HydrobJ.v45.i6.40" author="Genkal, SI" journalOrPublisher="Hydrobiological Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="51 - 69" refId="B43" refString="Genkal, SI, Terenko, LM, Nesterova, DA, 2009. New data on flora of centric diatoms (Centrophyceae) of the Danube area of the Black Sea. Hydrobiological Journal 45 (4): 51 - 69, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1615/HydrobJ.v45.i6.40" title="New data on flora of centric diatoms (Centrophyceae) of the Danube area of the Black Sea." url="https://doi.org/10.1615/HydrobJ.v45.i6.40" volume="45" year="2009">Genkal et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Tsarenko, PM" journalOrPublisher="Gantner Verlag, Ruggell" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B127" refString="Tsarenko, PM, Wasser, SP, Nevo, E, 2009. Algae of Ukraine: diversity, nomenclature, taxonomy, ecology and geography. Vol. 2. Bacillariophyta. A.R.A. Gantner Verlag, Ruggell" title="Algae of Ukraine: diversity, nomenclature, taxonomy, ecology and geography. Vol. 2. Bacillariophyta. A. R. A." year="2009">Tsarenko et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1615/HydrobJ.v50.i4.40" author="Genkal, SI" journalOrPublisher="Hydrobiological Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="38 - 49" refId="B42" refString="Genkal, SI, Terenko, LM, 2014. New data on flora of centric diatoms (Centrophyceae) of the Black Sea. Hydrobiological Journal 50 (2): 38 - 49, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1615/HydrobJ.v50.i4.40" title="New data on flora of centric diatoms (Centrophyceae) of the Black Sea." url="https://doi.org/10.1615/HydrobJ.v50.i4.40" volume="50" year="2014">Genkal and Terenko 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
As for general distribution, this taxon has only a few records around the world - Europe (Russia, Ukraine), Asia (Armenia, Russia), Africa (Egypt) (
<bibRefCitation author="Kulikovskiy, M" journalOrPublisher="Filigran, Yaroslavl" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B78" refString="Kulikovskiy, M, Glushchenko, AM, Kuznetsova, IV, Genkal, SI, 2016. [Identification book of diatoms from Russia]. Filigran, Yaroslavl" title="[Identification book of diatoms from Russia]." year="2016">Kulikovskiy et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Genkal, SI" journalOrPublisher="Filigran, Yaroslavl" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B45" refString="Genkal, SI, Kulikovskiy, MS, Kuznetsova, IV, 2020. Modern freshwater centric diatom algae in Russia [Sovremennye presnovodnye centricheskie diatomovye vodorosli Rossii]. Filigran, Yaroslavl" title="Modern freshwater centric diatom algae in Russia [Sovremennye presnovodnye centricheskie diatomovye vodorosli Rossii]." year="2020">Genkal et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Houk, V" editor="Poulickova, A" journalOrPublisher=")" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 529" refId="B61" refString="Houk, V, Klee, R, Tanaka, H, 2014. Atlas of freshwater centric diatoms with a brief key and descriptions Part IV., Stephanodiscaceae B: Stephanodicsus, Cyclostephanos, Pliocaenicus, Hemistephanos, Stephanocostis, Mesodictyon &amp; Spicaticribra. In: Poulickova, A, Ed., Fottea 14 (Suppl.): 1 - 529" title="Atlas of freshwater centric diatoms with a brief key and descriptions Part IV., Stephanodiscaceae B: Stephanodicsus, Cyclostephanos, Pliocaenicus, Hemistephanos, Stephanocostis, Mesodictyon &amp; Spicaticribra." volumeTitle="Fottea 14 (Suppl." year="2014">Houk et al. (2014)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. makarovae" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="makarovae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">S. makarovae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Genkal, SI" journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="241 - 248" refId="B37" refString="Genkal, SI, 2007. Morphology, taxonomy, ecology and distribution of small-sized species of the genus Stephanodiscus (Bacillariophyta). 2. Stephanodiscus makarovae. Botanical Journal 92 (2): 241 - 248" title="Morphology, taxonomy, ecology and distribution of small-sized species of the genus Stephanodiscus (Bacillariophyta). 2. Stephanodiscus makarovae." volume="92" year="2007">Genkal 2007</bibRefCitation>
) was erroneously included in the synonym 
<taxonomicName genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="C. delicatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="delicatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">C. delicatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Genkal) Casper &amp; Scheffler, since, according to the diagnosis, the marginal fultoportulae of 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. makarove" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="makarove">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">S. makarove</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have 2 satellite pores, and for 
<taxonomicName genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="C. delicatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="delicatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">C. delicatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
3. The difference in the number of satellite pores at the marginal fultoportulae in centric diatoms is a good diagnostic feature. For 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. makarovae" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="makarovae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">S. makarovae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the valve relief also varies from flat to slightly convex or concave, and there are also other morphological differences (see same publication 
<bibRefCitation author="Genkal, SI" journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="241 - 248" refId="B37" refString="Genkal, SI, 2007. Morphology, taxonomy, ecology and distribution of small-sized species of the genus Stephanodiscus (Bacillariophyta). 2. Stephanodiscus makarovae. Botanical Journal 92 (2): 241 - 248" title="Morphology, taxonomy, ecology and distribution of small-sized species of the genus Stephanodiscus (Bacillariophyta). 2. Stephanodiscus makarovae." volume="92" year="2007">Genkal 2007</bibRefCitation>
). As for the transfer of 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. makarovae" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="makarovae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">S. makarovae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Stephanodiscaceae" genus="Cyclostephanos" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cyclostephanos" order="Thalassiosirales" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Cyclostephanos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this is a debatable issue and molecular genetic studies are needed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
